            <title>[JDK-8314236] Overflow in Collections.rotate</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8314236</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>An integer overflow/wraparound in Collections.rotate() can lead to IndexOutOfBoundsException. Reproducer:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;// need something like -Xmx16g&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Collections.rotate(new ArrayList&amp;lt;&amp;gt;(Collections.nCopies((1&amp;lt;&amp;lt;30)+1, &amp;quot;&amp;quot;)), 1&amp;lt;&amp;lt;30)&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
